1.github repository, "settings"→ pull till "Danger Zone", find "Change repository visibility"→ "change to private"

2.gitfront.io→ "get started"→ "add repository"→ fill repository url→ "add"→ "convert to SSH"→ "copy"

3.go back to repository, "settings"→ find "Deploy keys" in the side bar→ "add deploy key"→ name it (eg: "read-only"), paste key in step 2, choose or not choose "allow write access"→ "add key"

4.go back to gitfront page→ "build"→ "view"→ copy website of the new page, send to people needed

